deck: Powerful, ancient Aztek demigod who seeks battle with the strongest fighters.
description:
Origin

Necalli, the Emissary of the Gods, is an ancient, powerful and savage Aztek god, who periodically awakens to fight powerful and strong fighters and to costume their souls. In the distant past, Necalli encountered and fought the Warrior Prophet, an Aztek priest who made prophecies regarding Necalli and who he would fight in the future. Some of the prophecies include encounters between Necalli and Ryu, Dhalsim and M. Bison.

Creation

Necalli was created by Capcom, and first appeared in the fifth installment of the video game franchise Street Fighter, 2016's Street Fighter V.

A Shadow Falls

In SFV's Cinematic Story Mode, he first appears in Nash's dream, in the form of a sheep. Necalli shouts 'devour' before he transforms back to his original shape and tries to devour Nash's soul. However a butterfly repels him.

Later, he appears before Ryu and Dhalsim in India; he then announces himself as 'the Jaws of Death' and says that the warriors' souls will come with him. Ryu faces him but as Necalli unleashes his full power, he gets soundly beaten. Ryu lets the Satsui no Hado get the best of him for a brief moment, but his blow gets blocked by Dhalsim, who teleported in order to hold back Necalli. The battle gets to a total halt as an outlandish object - a Black Moon made by Shadaloo - appears blocking the sun, making Necalli retreat.

Necalli then appears at Shadaloo's base before Bison, as he was about to finish Nash. The dictator then faces and defeats the beast, as he says everything goes according to his plan. Before Necalli could do anything else, Bison's second-in-command F.A.N.G repels him with his poison, making him retreat yet again. He then meets and then pursues Nash, Rashid and Azam, probably trying to devour their souls as well, but ultimately failing to do so as they escape in Karin's helicopter.

Later on, he has a final showdown with Ryu at the Kanzuki Zaibatsu. Ryu, being more confident in his training this time around, has an easier time facing the demigod. Ryu then channels the full extent of his Hado, which turns from purple/red (Satsui no Hado) into blue, indicating that he has achieved the Power of Nothingness. Necalli tries to attack Ryu, but he gets hit with a powerful blow. Necalli gets depowered, wondering why he couldn't devour his soul like he could with others. As Ryu doesn't struggle with the Red Energy/Satsui no Hado anymore, Necalli is said by Dhalsim that he won't be devouring Ryu's soul - or Dhalsim's or Bison's for that matter - after all. Failing to fulfill the prophecy, he finally dissipates to the ground for good.

Character Development

Necalli is inspired and influenced by several and various Aztek mythological figures, such as Huitzilopochtli and Tzitzimitl, as well as broader Aztek art, patterns and ideas. He has a very savage and violent personality, and dislikes humanity.

Other Media

Street Fighter V (2016)

Necalli first appears in Street Fighter V, alongside other new characters Laura Matsuda, F.A.N.G and Rashid.
name: Necalli

deck: Laura Matsuda is a free-spirited woman who wants to continue her heritage of Matsuda Jiu-Jitsu, hoping to promote it for others to follow. Sean is her younger brother.
description:
Origin

Laura is a Brazilian fighter, who was taught a family specialized style of martial arts referred to as Matsuda Jiu-Jitsu by her grandfather. The style which closely resembles Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu was also taught to her young brother Sean Matsuda. Laura is free spirited and friendly despite her main occupation and hobby, but is also proud of her families fighting style, and so wishes to promote and showcase it to the world and other fighters.

Creation

Laura Matsuda was created by Capcom, first appearing in its juggernaut video game franchise Street Fighter, specifically 2016's Street Fighter V.

Character Development

Laura is mostly characterized by her Brazilian nationality and pride in Matsuda Jiu-Jitsu. As a new character, she received a lot of attention and focus alongside other new characters Necalli, Rashid and F.A.N.G. She is adorned in Brazilian colored gear.

Other Media

Street Fighter V (2016)

Laura's debut in the fighting game series. She is voiced by G.K. Bowes and Yoko Hikasa.
name: Laura

description:
Patrick Kent was brought up from a prestigious American Southern family under the patriarch of industrialist Prescott Kent, who was closely involved in a conspiracy in overthrowing the FDR administration in place of a fascist government modeled after Nazi Germany but was foiled by Peter Cassaday, a then incarnation of Citizen Soldier. Kent was raised in a racist background in which he became a member of the Ku Klux Klan in which, as a teenager, he participated in the murder and lynching of an African-American family which their son was also another incarnation of Citizen Soldier, who was personally killed by Kent.

At his adult age, Kent became President and under his powers he was considered to be fairly corrupted, and as well being a lecherous adulterer and somewhat incompetent. During his tenure he created the Civil Defense Administration in response to threats to the United States, especially in regarding to superhuman terrorism, in which he appointed Ivana Baiul as head of the CDA. Ultimately, Kent's presidency was put in dire jeopardy when the recent incarnation of Citizen Soldier revealed his past and affiliation to the KKK as part of his plan to destroy the present establishment of the American government. The situation was investigated by the United Nations organization Team Achilles. When Citizen Soldier was killed in which he would reincarnated into a newborn American baby, Kent gave his permission to Baiul in murdering every newborn baby to prevent Citizen Soldier's rebirth. This was stopped by Team Achilles in which their leader Ben Santini threatened Kent from killing the babies and gladly have his team-member Flint to personally kill the President.

Later on, Kent's decision making ultimately led to his own downfall after the criminal mastermind Tao and his Syndicate deliberately gave the American government an engine that would allow them to explore the Bleed. A U.S. Space Program used the engine to launch a probe into the Bleed only for the engine to explode and causing a rift in the Bleed which led to almost bringing Earth into a inter-dimensional war with an alien race called the Vigil. In response, The Authority took matters into their own hands in which they avert this war by putting the blame on President Kent and his government, and began a coup d'etat in inserting their rule over the U.S. In response, Kent desperately had his military to oppose The Authority but was ultimately fruitless. He was then apprehended and executed by The Authority in order to placate the aliens. Although, the footage that were present to incriminate Kent were doctored as a convincing way to avert the war.
name: Patrick Kent

deck: Kid Reaper was Wendell Vaughn's personal Death Avatar
description:
Kid Reaper fist appeared to Quasar as he was pinned to a wall and dying after Phobius whipped him repeatedly with an energy whip after having his hands cut off by Maelstrom.

Kid Reaper ended that last little ember of lifeforce that Wendell was still defiantly clinging to with a sudden stab to Wendell's heart with his scythe.

Much later, an energy wraith manifestation bearing Quasar's appearance and seeming to be in some sort of trance simply floated out in the outer void. Kid Reaper suddenly appeared nearby and openly questioned the energy manifestation as though it was truly Quasar. Awakened from his stupor, Quasar asked Kid Reaper what this place was and why he wasn't dead. Kid Reaper pled ignorance saying that "Nothing like this had ever happened to him before". In a flash, Quasar realizes that Eon is still in danger and that it is his duty (even in death) to protect him. Quasar asks Reaper to hold open his cape. He says he finally knows what it is for." and he travels into it- using it as a portal...

Quasar along with Kid Reaper quickly arrived at the base of Eon’s brain, which is about the size of a planetoid, where Maelstrom reclines in a (Quantum-created) chair and has created various probes into the gray matter. Maelstrom hears Eon explain where Quasar should fire a blast that would result in immediate death for Eon. Maelstrom howls in rage at the sudden re-appearance of his adversary and attempts to blast him into nothingness (with the recently acquired Quantum-Bands), but since the energy-wraith Quasar is made from the same energy type that the Quantum-Bands produce the beam passes harmlessly through him. Quasar believing that it was Eon who was animating his form asked Kid Reaper to alert the Avengers to Maelstrom's threat and Kid Reaper agrees. Quasar responds by heeding his mentor’s wishes and firing a devastating bolt of energy right into Eon’s Brain stem.

When the dust clears, there is a gaping crater where Eon's brainstem used to be. Maelstrom howls in rage at apparently denied the secret of Cosmic Awareness. Quasar to his surprise still existed and found that his awareness is expanding as stars start to form on his face. Maelstrom understood that Eon had in his last act given the secret of Cosmic Awareness to his protector and quickly demanded that Quasar give it to Maelstrom. Knowing that Maelstrom could not threaten him anymore, Quasar refused. Changing tactics Maelstrom quantum-jumped out of the Eonverse to orbit of Earth where Quasar and Kid Reaper followed him.

Maelstrom halted the rotation of the Earth using his own power, the power of the anomaly and augmented that power with the Quantum-Bands, saying he'd only free the planet from imminent destruction only if Quasar would release Cosmic Awareness to him. Unable to gamble with his own home planet, Quasar retreated to the Quantum-Zone, leaving Kid Reaper behind.

It was then that Maelstrom revealed that he already had Cosmic Awareness and simply wanted Quasar to give his up. Maelstrom then sent Kid Reaper back to the realm of Oblivion.

Later, during the Infinity War, Quasar uses the Ultimate Nullifier and is nullified. Lost in the realm of Oblivion, Quasar is found by Kid Reaper again. Quasar attempts get Kid Reaper to assist him in escaping the realm, but Kid Reaper betrays Quasar and stabs him through the heart sending him to the White Room.

deck: Ulysses is a Nuhuman who can predict the future. He is the center around the new Civil War amongst the superhuman community.
description:
Origin

Ulysses was a young college students with an ordinary life until the terrigen mists that roam the Earth came to Ulysses' home town. While he was attending school, the mists covered them and Ulysses was revealed to be an Inhuman. His powers manifested not soon afterwards, a vision of a city in ruins due to an Celestial being whom threatened Earth.

Creation

Ulysses / Profiler was created by Brian Michael Bendis and Jim Cheung and first appeared (publishing-wise) in Marvel's Free Comic Book Day 2016 (Civil War II). His chronological first appearance and origin was revealed in Civil War II issue 0.

Major Story Arcs

Civil War II

Ulysses soon came to the attention of the superhero community. It was him that informed them of a coming threat of a celestial being that would threaten New York City. But when that threat was averted, the superhuman community became divided as to how use Ulysses' powers. Should they avert crimes before they are commited, technically puting people in jail before they even did anything, or use the information to be there the moment the crime is commited. Ulysses stands in the middle of the divided superhero community.

deck: An Iraqi girl who came to America to take revenge on the killers of her family.
description:
Origin

Ayah lived in the Ar Rutba district, Al Anbar, Iraq.She wanted to be a doctor, like her father. In late 2004, the district was under control of the U.S. Army. Officer Eric Foster, becoming slightly paranoid, believed his group was followed by the same car. He ordered the innocent drivers to be shot. Seeing two men flee the scene, Eric and his group ran after them. Eric and soldier Iris Gentry came across Ayah and her parents on a nearby rooftop. Eric shot Ayah's father and forced Iris to shoot Ayah and her mother.

As a dying gift, Ayah's mother transferred her powers to Ayah in the form of a crow, which burrowed itself inside Ayah thorugh her mouth.

Now, Ayah has followed Eric Foster's group of soldiers to the United States. With her newfound powers, she takes revenge on them by killing them one by one.

Major Story Arcs

Unbeknown to Iris Gentry, Ayah befriends his son Shiloh. They roam through the woods of Black Lick Hollow. She partly tells Shiloh her background. As Shiloh tells his father Iris about Ayah and where she comes from, he immediately is alarmed by it. Strange things have happened to Iris lately and he thinks they're connected. With Iris away from the house, Ayah attacks Iris' wife Sarah first but, when Sarah struggles free with the help of Elijah Cooper, Ayah abducts Shiloh instead.

Powers & Abilities

Ayah can trasform herself into a giant bird-like creature. During the transformation, her upper body separates itself from her lower body, wings sprout from her back and her arms become claws. A crow's beak portrudes out of her head. She can also use her intestines to strangle others.
